Context should make the meaning clear. Mnesi-  with the - tic suffix for medical agents it becomes mnestic. Which therefore is a drug that induces remembering. Adding the a- prefix would negate this and therefore amnestic would be a drug that induces forgetting. Since in the context the subjects are being expected to remember something, a drug that induces memory makes sense.





